<p style="text-align: right;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">        <a adhocenable="false" href="/Net/Documentum/processes/default.aspx">Back to Processes</a></span></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Our Responsible Lending obligations under the national Consumer Credit Protection Act require us to determine and record if the customer is aware of any future changes to their ability to make repayments without financial difficulty. Refer <a adhocenable="false" href="/Net/Documentum/regulatory-requirements/nccp.aspx">National Consumer Protection Act. </a></span></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">You will be prompted to use the scripting below to determine if the customer is aware of any future changes to their ability to make repayments without financial difficulty. </span></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">You will need to record the customer's responses by selecting the relevant options in the Application Software you use. </span></p>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><b>Notes: </b></span></p>
<ul>
<li style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Future Changes declaration must be completed for every credit product application as part  of the Bank's Responsible Lending Obligations under the National Consumer Credit Protection Act. </span></li>
<li style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">This question is not in relation to temporary decrease in income, permanent decrease in income or anticipated large expenditure that have been addressed in the application using mitigants<br/> </span></li>
<li style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">This question is for when customers will not be able to make their repayments without financial difficulty.<br/> </span></li>
<li style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">The only exceptions are: </span></li>
</ul>
<p style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"> </span></p>
<ol>
<li style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">The Future Changes declaration does not apply to application in a Company name or Trusts with a company as a trustee. </span></li>
</ol>
